Electric cars also have close to zero maintenance. That's thousands and thousands of dollars over the lifetime of the car + time + money not spent on fuel.

&#x200B;

Many people are unfortunately fools and they only look at the monthly loan cost without seeing how much insurance, gas, maintenance will cost.

You're right with that. EV charging will never be as quick as gassing up.

&#x200B;

However, there can be certain lower volume solutions. For example, NIO is running a successful subscription based service that swaps batteries in 5 minutes. The idea is that you don't pay for the battery in your car (so that cost is subtracted out of purchase) and pay monthly for a battery swap.
